# e-Malkhana environment overrides
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values for your
# deployment.  All variables are OPTIONAL — the server boots fine without
# them, falling back to the demo seed in server/store.js.

# HTTP port for the unified server (API + static frontend).
# Default: 4000
# PORT=4000

# ---- Postgres (Neon) ----
# Set this to the pooled connection string from the Neon dashboard:
#   1. Open https://console.neon.tech → your project → Connection details
#   2. Branch: production (Default), Role: neondb_owner, Database: neondb
#   3. "Connection pooling" ON, click "Copy snippet"
# The string looks like:
#   postgresql://neondb_owner:***@ep-xxx-pooler.<region>.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require&channel_binding=require
# Required in both .env (local) and Vercel env (production).
#
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://neondb_owner:...ep-...aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require&channel_binding=require

# ---- MM (Malkhana Moharrir) accounts override ----
# JSON array of {id, name, rank, designation, station, initials, password?}.
# When set, this REPLACES the demo seed users in server/store.js at boot.
# `password` is OPTIONAL — omit it for a passwordless account (suitable
# only for trusted internal networks).  For any internet-facing deployment
# set a non-empty `password` for every account.
#
# Example:
# MM_USERS=[{"id":"MM-001","name":"SI Rakesh Sharma","rank":"Sub-Inspector","designation":"Malkhana Moharrir","station":"PS Sector-5, Panchkula","initials":"RS","password":"set-a-real-one"}]
